Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of computer vision and deep learning techniques for automatic information extraction from camera trap images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of active learning, which involves selecting the most informative samples for labeling, and this falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of overfitting to specific image backgrounds, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of motion-activated cameras, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
